<subSubSection id="21143D79E6238AF8BDB63839794EAC16" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="30B7FFFAC9BA87A05470699AAB51C864" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Diagnosis and taxonomy</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D3DC201230279B32CF4455AD9E0DF8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
(Table 
<tableCitation id="8DE4FF95291F9096E6DB36DA9C40233B" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. RAV-corrected morphometric data of worker individuals of the Plagiolepis schmitzii complex given as arithmetic mean + / - standard deviation [minimum, maximum]; n = number of individuals. F values and significance levels p are from a univariate ANOVA and evaluate the differences between Pl. atlantis and Pl. invadens sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/D391BECA51134E5ACE149FBAA04D14FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" tableUuid="D391BECA51134E5ACE149FBAA04D14FB">1</tableCitation>
, key, AntWeb, 2020: pictures of specimens CASENT0912424 and CASENT0912428):
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11C5B2D7317D8751DB942092420387FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<taxonomicName id="0DA2B6A48F26C01295349D60C30E9A82" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. barbara" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis id="E281F13A19C75A4C57850E664C634790" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="1CE5B506EAE50275C78FCA82C83E6A01" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. schmitzii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="schmitzii">
<emphasis id="4F63E8F8CB2E145724E731F52BC3D13C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. schmitzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a much shorter scape and a shorter postocular distance, from 
<taxonomicName id="C7E9DCA4EB89EC51F58B2DA81521E896" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. atlantis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="atlantis">
<emphasis id="4EBA2BBF79BC51A6254242A72B1F54FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. atlantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by larger eye and from 
<taxonomicName id="A7FEAF620EA11013A0A104A4B30DF818" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. invadens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="invadens">
<emphasis id="390DD95BCD667BA3F629CC7474AB57DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. invadens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by larger eye and much longer 3rd funiculus segment. The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="FC93BE58A802A9F66D12D99E35229824" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. atlantis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="atlantis">
<emphasis id="957C325A1213B2DD3CA84D168D029D99" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. atlantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it may be asked if there is a risk of synonymy, considering the small sample size in 
<taxonomicName id="95E8839518C7D7E2C5B8EF7B1D6A8198" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. barbara" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis id="68346A9FD8558D9E28DB6533FE0BF6D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This risk is low.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1E088E71F352B872A7AE6871AD8B44B" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Running a PCA with absolute head size and the 16 RAV-corrected shape, pubescence and surface characters, there is a very strong separation of all individuals by the first principal component (ANOVA, F1,61 149.0, p &lt;&lt; 0.001):</paragraph>
<paragraph id="00C0E8F1AF5AC643D0D82B497AFB0708" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<taxonomicName id="073FE390C683D95821E0D38BFB5EBDB6" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. atlantis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="atlantis">
<emphasis id="BE618410670412E98A2EC4446988124D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. atlantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-0.295 
<normalizedToken id="653BCD7143A690F678DEE18AD5F131EC" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.532 [-1.337, 0.758] n = 56
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0707056A8296927BE0F7770977E9E709" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">
<taxonomicName id="2EE448F20CAEA699FD61C132D8305632" family="Formicidae" genus="Pl." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pl. barbara" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="183" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis id="D78178F25300BAEE269460248588E458" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="183">Pl. barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
2.363 
<normalizedToken id="C928C061D84C57A610A4B3BFCBF80E1D" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.638 [1.564, 3.311] n = 7
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
